commit.message:
Suppress AbortError in useSimpleEsqlQuery (#2203)

`useSimpleEsqlQuery` surfaces `AbortError` as a user-facing error
(`"AbortError: aborted"`) when React Query cancels in-flight requests
(e.g., rapid query key changes). The sibling hook `useEsqlQuery` already
suppresses this correctly.

- **`src/hooks/useSimpleEsqlQuery.ts`**: Add `DOMException`/`AbortError`
guard to the error mapping, returning `null` instead of the error
message — same pattern as `useEsqlQuery.ts:139`.
- **`tests/unit/useSimpleEsqlQuery.test.ts`**: Add test verifying
`AbortError` yields `error: null`.

```ts
if (rawError instanceof DOMException && rawError.name === "AbortError") return null;
```

